# Thanks to Chenglong Chen for providing this in the forum
def ToWeight(y):
    w = np.zeros(y.shape, dtype=float)
    ind = y != 0
    w[ind] = 1./(y[ind]**2)
    return w

def rmspe(yhat, y):
    w = ToWeight(y)
    rmspe = np.sqrt(np.mean( w * (y - yhat)**2 ))
    return rmspe

def rmspe_xg(yhat, y):
    # y = y.values
    y = y.get_label()
    y = np.exp(y) - 1
    yhat = np.exp(yhat) - 1
    w = ToWeight(y)
    rmspe = np.sqrt(np.mean(w * (y - yhat)**2))
    return "rmspe", rmspe

Removing outliers with values outside 4 standard deviations¶

In [136]:
# |(np.abs(store_1.Sales.mean())>(store_1.Sales + 3*store_1.Sales.std()))
final_train = pd.DataFrame()
#final_train = final_train.append(train_correct)
for a in tqdm(train.Store.drop_duplicates().tolist()):
    #store_1 = pd.DataFrame()
    store_1 = train[train['Store']==a]
    #std_dev = train['Sales'][train['Store']==a].std()
    store_1 = store_1[~((np.abs(store_1.Sales-store_1.Sales.mean())>(4*store_1.Sales.std()))|(np.abs(store_1.Sales.mean())>(store_1.Sales + 3.25*store_1.Sales.std())))]
    final_train = final_train.append(store_1).reset_index(drop = True)
